WEBVTT

00:00:00.160 --> 00:00:01.640
So as we go through this course,

00:00:01.660 --> 00:00:04.040
one of the things that you'll see is that we really focus

00:00:04.040 --> 00:00:06.260
on the core ideas and principles that you need

00:00:06.260 --> 00:00:07.900
throughout the landscape of AI.

00:00:08.440 --> 00:00:11.060
The way that I've heard it framed on UK's campus

00:00:11.060 --> 00:00:12.560
is to be tech agnostic,

00:00:12.560 --> 00:00:15.180
which I think is a really fancy way of saying,

00:00:15.400 --> 00:00:19.700
don't just learn how to drive this one specific car,

00:00:19.960 --> 00:00:23.540
because everything is changing in all the AI cars, all the time.

00:00:23.540 --> 00:00:26.220
What do you need to learn how to drive any car,

00:00:26.220 --> 00:00:30.560
to use any AI tool, and then building out
specific tools and skill sets from there?
